."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Barbara","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin, meaning ‘foreign woman’ (a feminine form of <i>barbarus</i> ‘foreign’, from Greek, referring originally to the unintelligible chatter of foreigners, which sounded to the Greek ear like no more than <i>bar-bar</i>).  St Barbara  has always been one of the most popular saints in the calendar, although there is some doubt whether she ever actually existed. According to legend, she was imprisoned in a tower and later murdered by her father, who was then struck down by a bolt of lightning. Accordingly, she is the patron of architects, stonemasons, and fortifications, and of firework makers, artillerymen, and gunpowder magazines."],"variants":[{"name":"Barbra","meanings":["From Latin, meaning ‘foreign woman’ (a feminine form of <i>barbarus</i> ‘foreign’, from Greek, referring originally to the unintelligible chatter of foreigners, which sounded to the Greek ear like no more than <i>bar-bar</i>).  St Barbara  has always been one of the most popular saints in the calendar, although there is some doubt whether she ever actually existed. According to legend, she was imprisoned in a tower and later murdered by her father, who was then struck down by a bolt of lightning. Accordingly, she is the patron of architects, stonemasons, and fortifications, and of firework makers, artillerymen, and gunpowder magazines."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1670166,"age":9,"year":"1682","julianDay":2335399,"title":"The Palace of Versailles","description":"The Palace of Versailles was originally known as a hunting log and retreat for Louis XII. When Louis XIV took over he moved his family into it. After he died the palace was abandoned. It has since been turned into a museum.","url":"https://www.britannica.com/topic/Palace-of-Versailles","urlTitle":"Encyclopedia Britannica- Palace of Versailles","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1670191,"age":27,"year":"1700","toYear":"1792","julianDay":2341973,"title":"French Monarchy","description":"The French monarchy started way before the 1700s, but for the most part the major events of history took place during this time before the French Revolution started. This was known as the Bourbon Dynasty. Louis XIV the Great, Louis XV the Beloved, Louis XVI the Restorer of French Liberty, and Louis XVII all reigned during this time.","url":"https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmXoypizjW3WknFiJnKLwHCnL72vedxjQkDDP1mXWo6uco/wiki/Kingdom_of_France.html","urlTitle":"Kingdom of France","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1670112,"age":105,"year":"1778","julianDay":2370462,"title":"Treaty of Alliance with American Colonies","description":"After the battle of Saratoga France realized that America might be worth backing. They formed an alliance with the colonies and sent naval fleets to help with the war.","url":"https://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/franco-american-alliances-signed","urlTitle":"History-Franco-American Alliances Signed","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1670116,"age":110,"year":"1783","julianDay":2372288,"title":"Treaty of Paris is Signed ","description":"While Benjamin Franklin was the ambassador to France he negotiated with the French during the war to keep them on the American side. At the same time the Treaty of Paris was established.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/american-revolution/treaty-of-paris","urlTitle":"History-Treay of Paris","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Anna Maria Barbara was born on 16 October 1672, in Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France. She married Johann Georg Schumacher about 1693, in Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France. They were the parents of at least 5 sons and 2 daughters. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"16 October 1672–":"16. oktoober 1672–Surnud","1675–1733":"1675–1733","1693–1767":"1693–1767","1700–1750":"1700–1750","1703–1769":"1703–1769","1705–1749":"1705–1749","1708–Female":"1708–Surnud","1710–1749":"1710–1749","1712–1769":